commit.message:
Update `allow_failures`

Ruby 2.3 is not yet available on Travis-CI, and jruby-head looks
unstable for now.
Fix tests for compatibility with ruby 1.8.7
Update the list of rubies to test with
Use the latest bundler on Travis-CI

Make the default `http_get` proc act more like Googlebot

- It only allows up to 5 redirect hops rather than 10.
- It treats too many redirections as full allow.
- It treats any 4xx error as full allow.

cf. https://developers.google.com/webmasters/control-crawl-index/docs/robots_txt?hl=en
Follow the deprecation warning from SimpleCov::Formatter::MultiFormatter
Update real world tests, introducing Webmock+VCR
Travis's ruby-head environment is still so broken.
Attemps don't seem to work.  Disable coveralls for JRuby on Travis.
Attempt to exclude jruby run without JRUBY_OPTS.
Keep rdoc away from *.ry which rdoc fails to process.
Add rake as development dependency.  Let's see if it satisfies Travis-CI.
